Patient Instructions: Diabetes and Kidney Disease.

Educated about HTN and that if left untreated or uncontolled eventually, it can lead to serious complications, such as heart attack, heart failure, stroke, kidney damage, and vision loss. Fortunately, lifestyle changes and/or medication can usually get blood pressure under control and reduce the risk of developing these problems. No added salt to diet and check BP's daily.

Labs: A1c 8.8. Last one 7.4-office value (?). No preteinuria. Continue present Rx.
Current medications: Novolog 70/30 35units q am and 25units q pm and Metformin 750mg tid.
VITAMIN D DEFICIENCY
Labs: Vitamin D25 12. Ca 8.7 (9.0).
Current medications: Started 3,000u qd.
ANEMIA SCREENING
Labs: CBC 6.2>43.8 (41.8)<254.
OPHTHALMOLOGY
Receives injections for eye disease monthly x 1 year.
LBP
Hx of Low back sx. Disabled bc of it.
LIPIDS SCREENING
Labs: Chol. 169 (170), Trig. 140 (108), HDL 38 (46), LDL 103 (102).
Patient educated on hyperlipidemia: High lipid levels can lead to atherosclerosis, or hardening of the arteries. Arteries are normally smooth on the inside, but with age, plaque forms in the walls of the arteries. Plaque is made of lipids and other materials circulating in the blood. As more plaque builds up, the arteries can narrow and stiffen. Eventually, enough plaque may build up to reduce blood flow through the arteries. Atherosclerosis increases your risk of heart disease, stroke, and other vascular diseases. Patient is to optimize dietary intake by limiting saturated fats and cholesterol and attempt to lose weight. Educated on alternatives to do so. Attempt to eat more green vegetables and less fried food.
NO OBESITY
Pt. educated on the many medical problems associated with obesity and are at increased risk for the following: reduced life expectancy, DM, gallstones, HTN, osteoarthritis, coronary heart disease, abnormal blood lipids, stroke, sleep apnea and certain cancers. Advised to decrease portions and eat more fruits and vegetables. Encouraged to exercise regularly as tolerated.
